Babu was abandoned by his family because he got severe mange. Babu was beaten by the locals because of smell which was coming out from him. We rescued him on time & started his treatment. Babu is up for adoption but only for colder regions. Mean while if someone would like to adopt babu virtually so one can become his virtual parent by donating Rs. 2,500 per month. Please share this video to make people understand that we shouldn’t remove a dog from his natural habitat. 

#healingsaathi #mugdhakhatri #dehradun #support #rescuedogs #rescuedogsofinstagram #adoptdontshop

Mini's was a 5 years old female dog who was living happily in Gol market area near Mohabbewala, Dehradun along with her friends. People of that area loved her so much. But today Mini was brutally murdered. She was attacked with a sickle. She was rushed to the clinic by Mr. Abhishek, an animal lover. She was provided treatment but unfortunately she couldn’t be saved. 

FIR has been registered against the accused under the guidance of SPCA vice president Ms. Pooja Bahukhandi. Thank you so much Vansh Tyagi, Reema, Sonali Talwar, Mr. Inderjeet Singh Vasudev & Healing Saathi for staying United & followed the procedure legally. 

Mini's caretakers (Abhishek and other people of that area) are very devasted and we all demand justice for her.

#animalcruelty #dogcruelty #animalwelfare

latestPosts.caption:
Babu’s Transformation😍.
Babu a Bhotiya dog was rescued by us in Dehradun. He was thrown out on road by his owners because he was suffering from skin infection. On road his skin infection got worse and he started smelling a lot.

He used to take shelter in near by shops but people started beating him due to his body smell. 

Luckily one day we received a call for his rescue and now you can see how his life got completely changed.

Babu is so adorable, playful and favourite of everyone. Currently he is in our shelter home @healingsaathi

You can watch his recovery video on our profile - @healingsaathi / @mugdha_khatri 

To donate for our cause kindly visit the link in my bio.

Babli ki khushi ka thikana nahi rahta jab bhi wo @mayank.maithani ko dekhti hai. 
Bina koi condition itna pyar in bejubano ko ache se karna aata hai.

Follow us for more rescue stories.

Babli ki tarah hamari sanctuary me 200 se zyada dogs and cats hain aur sabke sab bahut pyare hain. In sabko aapke pyar aur support ki zarurat hai.

So keep supporting 🫶

Babli’s joy knows no bounds whenever she sees Mayank. These speechless creatures know how to love unconditionally.

Like Babli, our sanctuary is home to over 200 dogs and cats, all of whom are incredibly lovable. They all need your love and support.

Unconditional Love. Animal human bonding. Dog love.

We are receiving a large lot of hay today, and we’ve also secured a sponsor for boris (jute bags).

We need volunteers to visit our sanctuary and help us make bori beds for our street animals. You’re also welcome to take these beds for street animals in your area to keep them warm and comfortable.

Alternatively, if you know someone who can help us make bori beds for street animals at the lowest possible cost, please DM us.

Thank you for your support!

Urgent Help Needed to Clear November Dues

Dear Supporters,

As the year comes to an end, we are facing an urgent need to clear our outstanding payments to ensure the continuation of care and support for the animals at Healing Saathi. We have five critical dues that need immediate attention:
	•	Vet Lab: ₹58,220
	•	Gulri Feed Suppliers: ₹1,57,973
	•	Ganesh Pharma: ₹47,482
	•	Eva Vets: ₹1,28,933
	•	Tej Ram Bhushan Lal: ₹42,000

The total amount has become overwhelming, and many vendors are urgently requesting payments. We kindly request your support to help us clear these dues. You can choose to contribute directly to Healing Saathi or send money directly to the respective vendors.

Every contribution, no matter the size, makes a significant difference. If you’d like to help or need details for direct payments, please reach out to us.

Thank you for always standing by us and the animals. Together, we can ensure they continue to receive the love and care they deserve.

Warm regards,
Team Healing Saathi
